Sarah Gabor

External
Inbox

Mike Lenard
12:32 PM (4 hours ago)
to me

Good Afternoon Sean

We have an 2017 Ford Edge 2.0 Ecoboost in the shop. Current mileage is 120551km.  The engine consumes coolant with a white smoke on start up after sitting. It ran fine for a day and the condition came back. We have conducted the normal diagnostic procedure but couldn’t pin the problem down. I’ve contacted Ford and was informed that these engines are suffering from a porous block and there was a TSB on the problem. The car is out of the Ford coverage so the cheapest fix is to install a used engine with a later engine number (past the TSB range) . I’ve found a used unit for $2150.00 the Alldata labor is 11.2 for the R&R at $110hr.  2150+1232=3382=txs. Her coverage is capped at $3000.00 so she’ll have to pay outstanding amount for deductible , diagnosis taxes etc.

 

Mike Lenard
Fixed Operations Manager
